        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/6–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Batavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-28T18:00:00-04:00">June 28, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>350. Personal for Cochran from Secretary: I want you to have my own
                    congratulations on your outstanding job in achievement of mutually satisfactory
                    arrangements between Repub and Neth for implementation May 7 agreement and for
                        <gloss target="#t_RTC1">RTC</gloss>. I wholeheartedly share with all <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> officers who have been following developments
                    their admiration for your skillful handling of an extremely difficult situation.
                    You have realized the primary condition for final peaceful settlement Neth–Repub
                    dispute.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
